Q,8 --  Describe the 3 main steps of a RAG pipeline in the correct order.
Be clear about what happens at ingestion time (when you load documents) vs query time (when a user asks a question).

A,8 -- after upload of your pdf/docs file the rag go in this order: chunking,embedding,vectorstore,retriever,and then you build the chain.
first: chunking, split the text into sentences array as the defined splitter you choose.
second: embedding, convert the sentences array into vector_db by OPENAI_KEY or HUGGINGFACE_KEY or local docker-compose.
third: vectorstore, you store your vectors with chroma then you can define your retriever with as_retriever function.
forth: retriever, you define your retriever(the object that pull the answer) right after you define your vectorstore with croma.
you have a few methods of retriever but we use chroma so the retriever is plain function in this chroma object(using the distance cosine (1-cosine similarity)).

